# ACM - AcmeEats Scrapy Project (ConSo)

Scrapy project for scraping restaurant listings and menu data from AcmeEats,
covering United States and Canada. Collects outlet information, meal items,
and meal options via the AcmeEats mobile API.

> **Branch:** This repository runs on the `feature/conso` branch, which depends on
> `dashmote_sourcing@feature/conso` and deploys via GitHub Actions → ECR → ECS Fargate.

## Overview

**Platform:** ACM<br>
**Platform Name:** AcmeEats<br>
**Official Website:** [acmeeats.com](https://www.acmeeats.com)<br>

**Service Availability:** 🇺🇸 United States (US), 🇨🇦 Canada (CA)<br>
**Supported Devices:** Mobile

### ConSo Architecture

This project runs two spiders in sequence:

1. **`conso_outlet_finder`** — Iterates over geo-grid points (lat/lon) from Redis and
   calls the AcmeEats search API to discover restaurant IDs near each point. Discovered
   outlets are written to MySQL via `RDS_PIPELINE`.

2. **`conso_outlet_detail`** — Reads outlet IDs from MySQL, fetches full restaurant
   detail (name, address, hours) and menu data (meals + options) in a two-step request
   chain. Output is written to S3 as Parquet via `S3_PIPELINE`.

### API Information

| Name | Method | Type | Platform | Spider | Auth | Proxy | Description |
|------|--------|------|----------|--------|:-----|:------|:------------|
| Search Nearby | GET | API | Mobile | finder | Bearer | Yes | Discover restaurants near a lat/lon grid point |
| Restaurant Detail | GET | API | Mobile | detail | Bearer | Yes | Fetch name, address, coordinates, hours, and ratings |
| Menu | GET | API | Mobile | detail | Bearer | Yes | Fetch full menu tree (categories → meals → options) |

### Request Flow Diagram

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[start_requests<br/>pop grid from Redis] -->|lat, lon| B[parse<br/>search API]
    B -->|id_outlet, country| C[FeedItem → MySQL]

    D[start_requests<br/>pop id_outlet from Redis] -->|id_outlet, outlet_data| E[_build_request<br/>detail API]
    E --> F[parse<br/>outlet_information]
    F -->|id_outlet| G[parse_menu<br/>menu API]
    G --> H[OutletItem → S3]
    G --> I[MealItem × N → S3]
    I -->|id_meal| J[OptionItem × M → S3]
```

### Important Notes

1. **Bearer token rotation:** The mobile API requires a short-lived Bearer token
   obtained from the `/auth/token` endpoint using a device fingerprint. Token refresh
   is handled inside `_get_token()` and cached per spider instance.
2. **Menu pagination:** The menu API returns up to 50 items per page. `parse_menu`
   follows `nextPageToken` until exhausted.
3. **Closed restaurants:** Outlets with `"status": "CLOSED_PERMANENTLY"` are yielded
   with `closed=True` and no menu requests are made — reduces wasted requests by ~8%.

